{"review": [{"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 0, "sentence": "This paper proposes an extension to the continual learning framework using existing variational continual learning (VCL) as the base method."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 1, "sentence": "In particular, it proposes to use the weight of evidence (WE) (from Zintgraf et al 2017) for each task."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 2, "sentence": "Firstly, this WE can be used to visualize the learned model (as used in Zintgraf et. al. 2017)."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 3, "sentence": "The novelty of this paper is:"}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 4, "sentence": "1. to use this WE from the current task to generate a silence map (by smoothing the WE) for the next task."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 5, "sentence": "This is interpreted the learned the learned attention region."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 6, "sentence": "Such an approach is named Interpretable COntinual Learning (ICL)"}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 7, "sentence": "2. The paper proposes a metric for the saliency map naming FSM which is an extension of existing metric SSR."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 8, "sentence": "The extension is to take pixel count to compute the area instead of using rectangular region area, as well as taking the distance between pixels into account."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 9, "sentence": "This metric can be used to evaluate the level of catastrophic forgetting."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 10, "sentence": "Pro:"}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 11, "sentence": "In general, the idea is very intuitive and make sense."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 12, "sentence": "The paper also demonstrates superior performance with the proposed method on continual learning on all classic tasks comparing with VCL and EWC."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 13, "sentence": "The presentation is very easy to follow."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 14, "sentence": "It seems like a valid and flexible extension that can be used in other continual learning frameworks."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 15, "sentence": "Cons:"}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 16, "sentence": "The theoretical contribution is very limited."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 17, "sentence": "The work is rather incremental from current state-of-the-art methods."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 18, "sentence": "There should be a better discussion of related work on the topic."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 19, "sentence": "The paper currently only mentions the most related work for the proposed method,  using the whole section 2 to describe VCL and use section 3 to describe FSM and half of section 5 to describe SSR."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 20, "sentence": "A general overview of related work in these directions are needed."}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 21, "sentence": "Other:"}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 22, "sentence": "1. The paper should also consider more recently proposed evaluation metrics such as discussed in https://arxiv.org/pdf/1805.09733.pdf"}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 23, "sentence": "2. The author should try to avoid using yellow color in plots."}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 0, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 1, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 2, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 3, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 4, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 5, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 6, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 7, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 8, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 9, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 10, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 11, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Motivation/Impact", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 12, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Substance", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 13, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 14, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Motivation/Impact", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 15, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 16, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Originality", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 17, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Originality", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 18, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Meaningful Comparison", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 19, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Meaningful Comparison", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 20, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 21, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 22, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Experiment", "asp": "Replicability", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "ryg4Fgr9hX", "sid": 23, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Edit", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}], "rebuttal": [{"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 0, "sentence": "We thank the reviewer for their time and welcome feedback, which we are incorporating into the revised version."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 1, "sentence": "R: - Theoretical contribution"}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 2, "sentence": "A:"}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 3, "sentence": "-- Just a clarification regarding the first contribution: WE from the current task is not used to generate a saliency map for the next task; it is instead used to instruct the learner of the next task about which input areas are more important than others via the attention mechanism."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 4, "sentence": "This becomes a part of the future learning procedure, not just a post hoc visualisation method as in the original WE ."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 5, "sentence": "As such, the first contribution is not solely about generating new visualisations; it is more about using the learned saliency maps from the past to attend in future learners."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 6, "sentence": "We therefore believe that the potential of this first contribution as a conceptual framework via which a learner can understand, attend, and then enhance its attention for future tasks, is not small."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 7, "sentence": "-- Importantly, we are the first to combine interpretability with continual learning and show that interpretability can help continual learning. It is a significant step to bring these two communities together."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 8, "sentence": "-- It is worth noting that VCL has achieved very good results on most of these benchmarks, so it is very hard to outperform it with a large margin."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 9, "sentence": "Nevertheless, although the experimental increases might not seem dramatic, they are statistically significant (we have added the statistical significance results to the appendix in the revised version)."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 10, "sentence": "R: - Related work"}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 11, "sentence": "A:"}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 12, "sentence": "-- Thank you."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 13, "sentence": "In addition to the locations specified by the reviewer, the first two paragraphs of Section 1 (especially the second paragraph) discuss several other related works."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 14, "sentence": "We have added more to the revised version."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 15, "sentence": "R: - https://arxiv.org/pdf/1805.09733.pdf"}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 16, "sentence": "A:"}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 17, "sentence": "-- Thank you. We have cited the paper in the revised version, and plan to take it into further consideration in future work."}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 18, "sentence": "R: - Yellow color in plots"}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 19, "sentence": "A:"}, {"text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 20, "sentence": "-- We have changed the yellow colour in Figures 2, 3 and 4 to black. Yellow is now no longer used in any plots."}], "rebuttallabels": [{"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 0}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 1}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 2}, {"labels": {"alignments": [4], "responsetype": "contradict-assertion", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 3}, {"labels": {"alignments": [4], "responsetype": "contradict-assertion", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 4}, {"labels": {"alignments": [4, 5, 6], "responsetype": "contradict-assertion", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 5}, {"labels": {"alignments": [4, 5, 6], "responsetype": "summary", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 6}, {"labels": {"alignments": [4, 5, 6], "responsetype": "summary", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "Bkggfq0VTm", "sid": 7}, {"labels": {"alignments": [17], "responsetype": "mitigate-criticism", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "Bkgg